{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:48:58.940Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data augmentation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a technique used to prevent overfitting by "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "increasing the diversity and quantity of training data"}, {"type": "text", "text": " through synthetic modifications of existing samples, forcing the model to learn more robust features instead of relying on irrelevant details or dataset-specific artifacts."}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple definition:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " \"Data augmentation is a technique used in machine learning to artificially increase the size of a dataset by creating new data points from existing data. This can be done by applying transformations to the data, such as cropping, rotating, or flipping images.\""}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Data Augmentation — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What overfitting is and why augmentation helps"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Overfitting"}, {"type": "text", "text": " occurs when a model "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "memorizes patterns"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in training data that don't generalize to new data, often due to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "limited or repetitive training examples"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model learns "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "noise"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "outliers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in training data"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Low training error but "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "high test error"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model is too "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "complex"}, {"type": "text", "text": " relative to the data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data augmentation combats overfitting"}, {"type": "text", "text": " by:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mechanism"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Effect"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Increases dataset diversity"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Exposes model to more variations of real-world scenarios"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Acts as regularization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": nu