ation, time stretching, volume adjustment\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "When to use"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Especially helpful for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "limited data"}, {"type": "text", "text": "; standard practice for CNNs, NLP, audio\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "When to avoid/caution"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Medical images (preserve anatomy), text with strict structure, extreme transformations that harm performance\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Combine with"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Cross-validation, early stopping, dropout, L2 regularization for robust overfitting defense\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best practice"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Use augmentation layers in model (GPU), tune intensity, ensure transformations preserve semantics\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Result"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": In one CNN study, augmentation increased "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "testing accuracy from 54.72% to 68.97%"}, {"type": "text", "text": " with limited data."}]}]}}